<br>
Mother Tunare was truly blessing Norrath this day with a beautiful sunrise.  Standing on the hill enjoying the morning, Phyllis thinks back to the days she had spent with Mezllo Quantemp, if anyone had been close enough they would have seen a small smile quickly vanish, but that is another time and place.<br>
<br>
She had completed her morning lessons and now she wanted to see what Norrath has in store for her, Mother Tunare willing.<br>
<br>
Making her way towards the Inn, a common stop for most travelers who were heading out into the wilds of the Commonlands, Phyllis spotted a fellow Bronze Dragon Fellowship member known as Rowin, another paladin.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tis a good sight you are to my eyes Phyllis&quot; Rowin said while approaching.<br>
<br>
Phyllis could easily see that he had been in some type of fight, &quot;I see. What happened to you Rowin, did you make yet another enemy or perhaps your girlfriend finally realized you are not the type to settle down?&quot;<br>
<br>
Grumbling to no one in particular, &quot;Humph, my girl friend. I should be so lucky,&quot; leaning forward and hugging Phyllis he continued with her towards the inn. &quot;I have been having other troubles though. A witch by the name of Iszabelle has been making accusations about our guild members and me. Her tongue drips venom.&quot;<br>
<br>
Suddenly feeling a chill run up her spine Phyllis glances around looking for someone or thing, but there was nothing around. &quot;Hum&quot; thinking out loud. <br>
<br>
&quot;What is it?&quot; Rowin inquired. <br>
<br>
&quot;Nothing sweetie&quot; stopping to open the inn door.' &quot;Now Rowin how can I help?&quot; said Phyllis<br>
<br>
Stepping in and waiting for Phyllis to follow Rowin continued, &quot;As I was saying the lady by the name of Iszabelle had a message for a female paladin within our guild. As fate would have it I ran into you good Phyllis for you see, the message she gave was meant for you!&quot;<br>
<br>
Raising an eyebrow, &quot;Me&quot; Phyllis looking interested, yet puzzled.  &quot;What was this message?&quot; she asked while handing the merchant a list of items she needed.<br>
<br>
&quot;Iszabelle told me that you have something of hers she wanted back&quot; pausing to look around, &quot;and that she would kill you to have it in her possession once again!&quot; Rowin said.<br>
<br>
&quot;I have nothing of value&quot; Phyllis answered back, &quot;you know we can not horde money and such. For it is against our vows.&quot;<br>
<br>
Turning quickly around facing the closed door with her blade ready, Phyllis scanned the area for any signs of someone hidden by magic, nothing. Shaking her head Phyllis was sure she had felt the breath of someone on the nape of her neck.<br>
<br>
Phyllis<br>
