<br>
&quot;Hum&quot; thinking to herself, &quot;the poor girl must not have received the news yet.&quot; This would be one more weapon she could use against the righteous paladin to break her with.<br>
Iszabelle watched as Phyllis and Rowin entered the Inn and could barely contain her excitement.<br>
<br>
She moved up closer to Phyllis. She was so close to Phyllis that she could smell the mild perfumes she had used earlier that morning. Iszabelle took a breath and kissed Phyllis on the nape of her neck. A tradition that her former master did right before she took their life.<br>
<br>
The shadows twisted and melted away from Iszabelle as she revealed herself. Rowin's eyes grew wide as he saw Iszabelle appear before Phyllis.<br>
<br>
Phyllis said, &quot;Greetings&quot;.<br>
<br>
Iszabelle grinned at Rowin and said &quot;Thanks for luring Phyllis here.&quot;<br>
<br>
Rowin stood up straight and grumble &quot;I did no such thing.&quot;<br>
<br>
Phyllis said &quot;He didn't lure me here and don't attack my friend with such accusations you venomous pit viper!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Phyllis don't be blinded by Rowins supposed good deeds&quot; trying her best to look honest, Iszabelle continued, &quot;you call me a pit viper and such is he!&quot;<br>
<br>
Seeing the look of anger on Rowin's face she pressed her point, &quot;Phyllis darling, he will turn against the guild as sure as day turns into night.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You foul witch,&quot; Rowin states firmly as he pulls forth his blade, &quot;you shall pay with your life for spreading such lies!&quot;<br>
<br>
Phyllis quickly steppes between the two, &quot;Do not let her words poison your thoughts Rowin, sheath thy blade.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Remember this! I shall only say it once. The Plague has come and it's our duty to wipe you and those of the light from the lands of Norrath, &quot; shouted Iszabelle.<br>
<br>
&quot;We shall cure this land of the blight called Plague Bringers. Pray thee Iszabelle that I can not get the guilds to unite against your kind,&quot; Phyllis says with the watchful eye of a trained warrior.<br>
<br>
Seeing that Phyllis was looking for an excuse to wield her blade against her, Iszabelle stepped back and the shadows swallowed her up.<br>
<br>
Phyllis' muscles visibly rippled as adrenaline pumped through her body in anticipation of battle.  Phyllis shouted out in anger &quot;Evil Spawn of Chaos show yourself! My blade shall drip with your blood and the Plague Bringers<br>
shall fall from the grace of their gods. Let the rivers run red with your blood so that others can see that your ways are wrong.&quot;<br>
<br>
Phyllis took a deep breath and shouted out &quot;You foul witch, I shall help you find your grave!&quot;<br>
<br>
Isazabelle spat out, &quot;'Tis my grave that gives me comfort. What shall I put on your tome!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You world is a web which entraps you more firmly as you struggle to control your pitiful, worthless life. And in the center of the web sits the Great Spider of your greed.  As it touches the strands of the web, you jerk like a<br>
puppet, and vainly believe that it is you who is in control of your destiny&quot;<br>
<br>
Phyllis shouts &quot;Then show yourself Iszabelle! Don't hide in the shadows! Lord Erollisi Mar shall judge thee!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Lies, Paladin! For even your greatest success is your ultimate failure. Your life is all but a mere illusion, wealth, fame, fortune are but fleeting things,&quot; Iszabelle said.<br>
<br>
Phyllis spat out in return,  &quot;My god protects me from your foul magic. I shall never become a ghoul who serves evil. Come Necro, I have a blade waiting to taste your blood.&quot;<br>
<br>
A tendril of thought crept into Iszabelle's mind.  Glancing around for a wizard or some other who might have might have charming magic. &quot;Vril, how dare you bother me now,&quot; almost dropping her veil of darkness Iszabelle forces her mind to focus and the shadows gather around her once again.<br>
<br>
&quot;Leave me be, Vril, &quot;Iszabelle's replies to Vril through the tenuous tendril of thought the weak wizard had established, &quot;I am going to finish off Connor's last daughter tonight.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;But Milady,&quot; Vril replied in a concerned manner, &quot;you must return. I can not explain, but you must.&quot;<br>
<br>
Sensing his anxiety, Iszabelle folds the shadows around herself. Reality parts and she gates.<br>
<br>
