<br>
&quot;KELEE&quot; shouted the bartender.  Kelee quickly pulled her drums out and sang Selo's to make a quick escape.  <br>
<br>
Kelee had enter the Commonland. It was such a beautiful day. Kelee took the time to walk to the nearby inn near the mountian. She noticed that many travelers were speaking of a possible fight near the inn.  Kelee being curious had began to sing Selo's to catch the action.<br>
<br>
As Kelee approached the end.  She had noticed a few of her fellow guild members.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Greetings Phyllis and Rowin&quot; Kelee said with a smile on her face as she hugged them both. &quot;What is this fight I hear about that is to take place?&quot; <br>
<br>
Phyllis's face was flushed. You could see the anger that grew. &quot;Phyllis let the angry go. Anger is a seed to the evil side.&quot; Kelee said as she started to sing Kelin's Lugubrious Lament to calm her down and for her to realize what was happening.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now what happened?&quot; Kelee raising and eyebrow.<br>
<br>
&quot;She gated just like that. We were to much competiton for her&quot; Rowin said loudly. <br>
<br>
&quot;Who?&quot; Kelee replied.<br>
<br>
&quot;Iszabelle is her name. All I know that she's evil and said that I have something of her's that she would kill for&quot; Phyllis said as she sat on the ground.<br>
<br>
&quot;I have heard of Iszabelle; however, I have not met this person. I will have to do some research to see if I can help you Phyllis&quot;  Kelee said as she place her hands on Phyllis's shoulders.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><img src=http://www.mmpog.net/EverQuest/BronzeDragon/Images/keleelogo.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cac3ab><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uiszabelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iszabelle</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.mmpog.net/EverQuest/BronzeDragon/Images/fadeskull.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>BDF Member</span><br>   <font color=#c54400>(7/22/00 6:02:21 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.mmpog.net/EverQuest/BronzeDragon/Images/Iszabelle.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Introduction to Bronze Dragon Fellowship</span><hr size=1> It had been weeks that Iszabelle had been on an adventure.  She heard from traveling bards that there was a gathering at Runnyeye.  She was nearby and decided to stop and take a look around.<br>
<br>
Iszabelle had enter a dark sinster dungeon. She could smell the dirty gnolls. Magic glistened around Iszbelle as she casted and she disappeared into the dark.  She was protected by the dark blanket and begun to explore the dungeon. She heard a group near the King's room.  Iszabelle recongized the guild name and was beginning to enjoy the night that she may able to take a soul. She had walked into the room.<br>
<br>
Iszabelle shouted &quot;I have come to take a soul.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Not as long as I am here!&quot; Molina shouted defensely. &quot;You'll have to go through me first.&quot;<br>
<br>
Iszabelle thinking to herself 'that can be arranged Molina'.<br>
<br>
Iszabelle laid eyes upon a wizard named Warpoet.  He was stunning. She begins to chant and a mystical light mist blanket the room.  Finally the room had cleared, Izabelle and Warpoet were alone. She begins to chant again. Warpoet aware of his action and unable to resist the spell, he leaned over and kissed Iszabelle.  Iszabelle giggled and was thinking 'I love this'. The light mist started to fade and members were returning.  In the shadow, a wolf appeared. Tweani grumbled, &quot;If Kelee was here, she would rip you apart&quot; as she lifted her paw to scratch behind her right ear.<br>
<br>
 <p><img
src=http://www.mmpog.net/EverQuest/BronzeDragon/Images/fadeskull.gif>
<img src=http://www.mmpog.net/EverQuest/BronzeDragon/Images/titleizzy.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ada07e><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uiszabelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iszabelle</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.mmpog.net/EverQuest/BronzeDragon/Images/fadeskull.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>BDF Member</span><br>   <font color=#c54400>(7/22/00 6:27:37 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.mmpog.net/EverQuest/BronzeDragon/Images/Iszabelle.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   A night Molina will remember</span><hr size=1> Molina grew weary and tired after a long day of traveling.  She had returned home and laid down to rest. She fell asleep not knowing what was about to happen.  <br>
<br>
Iszabelle waiting for the right moment to begin Molina's turmoil.  Realizing that she was fast asleep, Iszabelle began to chant.  The room filled with heavy blue mist, Molina began to dream.<br>
<br>
Molina had found herself wandering the woods. It was dark and cold.  She didn't recognize the area. In the distance, she caught a light flickering.  She slowly headed in that direction. She approached and notice a wood elf stripped of her armor. The wood elf moaned near the fire.  Three entities had surrounded the wood elf and lifted her upon the alter.  Molina stood frozen unable to move or help the wood elf. A Teir'dal came out and had tied the wood elf down and then he began to take out tools.  The wood elf released a cry of pain.  The Teir'dal began to carve a marking into the wood elf's shoulder. Molina recognized Iszabelle when she was her in the background watching.  Molina had to urged to jump and and to defend the wood elf but she was unable to.  Molina watched Iszabelle slowly walked to the wood elf.  Iszabelle had raise a bright glowing stone and placed it on the shoulder where the Teri'dal had finished carving.  The wood elf let a scream and had passed out.  Molina could feel the pain that she was going through.<br>
<br>
Molina tossing and turning in her sleep had awakened to a scream.  Molina's shoulder was burning.<br>
<br>
  <p><img
src=http://www.mmpog.net/EverQuest/BronzeDragon/Images/fadeskull.gif>
