<br>
&quot;MY PET!&quot;  Mildikin shouts.  &quot;NOOOOO!&quot;  Then the torture healer looks to the group, eyes glowing with darkness, a smile thirsty for blood, and a heart hungry for death.  Kelee starts playing the drum and says rapidly, &quot;Follow me!&quot;<br>
<br>
They litterally dash thier way through the edge of the forest as Kelee beated to the sounds of Selo's Accelorando, and they managed to outrun the vile undead and pass Rivervale's enterence before they knew it.<br>
<br>
Shortly after, we reach the stone walkway leading to Highhold Pass.  The grumble of the residant orcs filled that particular area.  As they walked into the Pass, the orcs were doing battle with an intrepid group.  Mildikin says, &quot;Okay, we can get by as long as that party is a distraction to the orcs.&quot;  They make it passed thier easily and sit to rest a spell.<br>
<br>
A small fire was set up and the party had a bite to eat and some rest.  Mildikin starts to set a small round object with what seems to be a wheel on the bottom.  The front of this strange little metal thing has a small hole on top and a larger hole with glass in the front.  &quot;What is that little thing?&quot; asks Molina.  &quot;It looks strange.&quot;   Mildikin chuckles and replies, &quot;It's one of my stalking probes.  Made it myself!  I'll be using it to scout the road ahead for any potential dangers.&quot;  He, then, closes his eyes, holds a hand out and snaps his fingers.  The probe immediately starts to move on its wheel down the chasmway of the Pass.<br>
<br>
The stalking probe moves its way past the guards and citizens who look at the thing oddly.  The stalking probe stops to view a male wood elven bard.  The probe hums in Mildikin's mind, &quot;Known humanoid being detected.... Verify identification...&quot;.  The haunting and romantic voice of the bard as he sings and plays his mandolin  and his shy dimeanor is what makes him truely distinguishable form any other bard in Norrath.  Mildikin says, &quot;Ah... I see.  Probe, return.&quot;  The probe comes back to him.<br>
<br>
&quot;What is it you saw?&quot;, Khaldoren inquires.  Mildikin mumbles, &quot;Never thought I'd see him anytime soon.  Heh...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Who?  Who?&quot;, Molina asks in anticipation.  &quot;Who did you see?&quot;<br>
<br>
Mildikin looks down the way and grins.  &quot;Lyrick's just around the corner.&quot;<br>
<br>
Just that moment, Lyrick runs around the corner and spots the BDF group.  He smiles, his deep dark brown eye glimmering with the light of the morning sun, looking slightly galiant and quite handsome.  &quot;Ah, I figured the metal thing was your's, Mildikin.  How do you all do?&quot;  He grins shyly.  &quot;It's nice to see you all again.&quot;, Lyrick says in his normal, quiet soothing voice. <p>Mildikin Quartzworth<BR>
