A look of curiosity came over Kelee's face. Kelee rejoined the crew at the camp. <p><img src=http://www.mmpog.net/images/kelee%20logo.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cac3ab><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/umolinaeverlost.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Molina Everlost</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>BDF Officer, Sister of the Initiates</span><br>   <font color=#c54400>(8/1/00 2:51:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: HighHold Keep</span><hr size=1> As, Kelee went off to talk with the man O'berton, I talked with the group standing here. &quot;By the look on Kelee's face, she must have some news for us&quot;, I said. <br>
<br>
While waiting on Kelee, I told the others I needed to stock up on some supplies and find the others, so they know of our journey and what we must do. With a link built of love, friendship and trust, I closed my eyes and sought to locate, Rashek, the one that brought all these mights warriors together, to do just as we were doing, to banish the world of evil. Rashek had not been heard from in several days and I needed his guidance. As I ran inside the keep to seek my supplies, I whisper &quot;Rashek, my dear friend, we need you, come to us.&quot; With a weak reply from Rashek, &quot;Kelee has told me of your quest, and I shall be with you soon, I must finish here in Lavastorm and then Chantrelle can bring you to me.&quot; In return I asked if Kuvanu with with him and he replied with a smile. <br>
