<br>
&quot;Bronze Dragon Fellowship&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes it is a great guild with many good people&quot; said the female elf thatt reminded Eldoren so much of home.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Could I join this guild?&quot; Eldoren asked.<br>
<br>
&quot;Let me ask Kelee.&quot; she said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Who is Kelee?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;One of the officers of the guild.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, ok.&quot; said Eldoren in excitment.<br>
<br>
&quot;She'll be here in a little while&quot; said Laylani.<br>
<br>
Eldoren talked with Laylani for a hour or so and learned more about her and the Bronze Dragons.  Finally Kelee arrived and she also was a female wood elf bardess.<br>
<br>
&quot;So you wish to join the Bronze Dragon Fellowship?&quot; said Kelee.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, I do.&quot; <br>
<br>
And the rest was history. <p><imgsrc=http://www.photoloft.com/view/exportImage.asp?s=xpage&i=2869836&w=250&h=173></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cac3ab><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/bbronzedragonfellowship75394.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=caddilstormheart>Caddil Stormheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>BDF Member</span><br>   <font color=#c54400>(8/2/00 12:11:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Another Joins The Alliance</span><hr size=1>    It was a nasty night tonight, one particularly evil, even for the dreadful lands of Kithikor Forest.  Caddil had done much for Marr this day, slaying the undead creatures of the night.  However, he was still not satisfied, he was looking for something.  Marr would reveal his destiny to himself in time he thought.  <br>
   Suddenly he saw flashes of purple light whip fast across the terrains ahead of him.  &quot;Only one person that could be causing that&quot; Caddil said wiht a smirk.  He ran after the light, although his Spirit of the Wolf was no match for it.  Hours later, he finally caught up with the mystical beats of a hand drum.  &quot;Hello there Kelee!, ahhh and Molina, Khaldron, and Mildikin! What brings you all here my friends.&quot;  <br>
   What a lucky night, Caddil thought to himself.  Kelee, one of the loveliest and captivating bards he knew. Molina, another elven beauty, and she knew it, that little tease he chuckles.  Mildikin, the quirky, but always reasonable and battle ready gnome. And Khaldron, one of the very few Caddil trusted to support him in heavy battle.  &quot;We are here on a quest of lightbringing,&quot; Kelee said soothingly.  &quot;Ahhh, this may be my big break,&quot; Caddil said.<br>
&quot;As a warrior of Marr, I volunteer my services to all that is truthful,&quot; Caddil said, in his noblest voice.  &quot;There are others that we will need friends, a party of six will not be able to overcome this foe, no matter how pure our hearts.&quot;  <br>
    The night faded away, as plans were made, and old times were thought upon...<br>
<br>
    Elsewhere, a greater threat was growing, waiting for our adventurers to stumble unexpectedly into it.  (comic bookish, I know, but hey gimme a break <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ada07e><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ukhaldron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khaldron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight, Order of The Scale</span><br>   <font color=#c54400>(8/2/00 3:30:15 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/khaldron/Oops.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: HighHold Keep</span><hr size=1> &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Khaldron's eyes widened as Molina collapsed into his arms.  Noticing for the first time, the throbing of malignant magic eminating from her shoulder.  Laying her gently upon the ground at his feet, he gently pulled back the cloth and armor to reveal an angry red swelling.  Growling, he opened himself up to the power of the gods, placing his hands over the welt, he closed his eyes, and reached out with his spirit.  &quot;Looking&quot; at the wound, he saw an inscription in his native tongue.  His clerical powers, not being strong enough to abolish the blight to Molina's body, he wrapped in a shroud of energy to try to hold back the effects.  Pouring energy into her wounds, he closed that which he could, though the blight still remained.  Growling with renewed effort, he sectioned it off again with the last of his energy, and withdrew his presence, watching her breathe more easily.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp With a look of determination in his eye, Khaldron stood, and lifted Molina to a nearby bed.  After covering her with blankets, and smoothing her hair, he turned to his companions.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I've done what I can,&quot; he said with a sigh.  &quot;But I can only do so much.  This is a powerful curse laid upon her, and I can not combat it alone.  Watch her.  See that no harm comes to her.  Kelee, sing to her your songs which mend the flesh and the soul.  She needs all the help she can get.  What I've done drains both myself and her, so she will sleep until her energy is replenished.  See that her rest is not disturbed.&quot;<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Sitting at the end of the bed, he closed his eyes, and once again, reached out to the gods, only this time, rather than drawing thier power into himself, he released his spirit to them.  He sought counsel with the gods.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp First, he sought Innoruuk, Prince of Hate, though he doubted anything would be revealed by him.  His spirit strolling through Innoruuk's tower in the plane of Hate, he shuddered at the sights he saw, but knew that showing any weakness would detfeat all purpose of coming here.  He half walked, half glided into Innoruuk's throne room, and as the Prince of Hatred's gaze fell upon him, he felt a shiver of apprehension and awe shake his spine.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;What brings you to me?&quot; Innoruuk spat seeing the priest who once called him master.  &quot;If you think I'll show you mercy for your kindness and let you back into the fold, be at easy that no soul would give me more pleasure to torment than yours.&quot;<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Khaldron knew that Innoruuk would not give him any information willingly.  Wit, and quick thinking would be nessecary to learn anything from him.  He picked his words carefully to try to pry as much information as he could.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Ah, Lord of Hate, you taught me better than that, when I was in your service.  I came not to ask anything of you, but to tell you of my grand accomplishment.  I have defeated a powerful curse, wroght by your own creations, and written in your name.&quot;<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Laughing spitefully, he described what he knew of the curse, careful not to make any statements that might lead Innoruuk to see through his ruse.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;You have failed in this quest little one,&quot;  Innoruuk chuckled, &quot;For while you may have beaten back the symptom, you've not yet cured the disease.  The stone was the key, and without it, your friend will never be free.  You can not pierce the viel between dreams and reality, you've lost this round!  Now be gone from my presence, the smell of kindness offends me.&quot;  With these words, Innoruuk waved a hand, and Khaldron was pushed from the room, and his spirit floated free in the void between the planes.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Next, he swept his soul to the temple of Rodcet Nife, and swam in the lakes, with the Kolandil Fish, until he approached one with a gleam intelligence in it's eye.  This one he swam up to, and queried.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Hello, Prime Healer?&quot; He asked hopefully, &quot;I've need of one of your knowledge in combatting an evil curse.&quot;<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The fish looked at him quizically and then dipped it's head, and then Khaldron was floating in a small cozy room, with two large comfortable chairs, and cheery fire crackling in a fireplace.  In one of these chairs sat Rodcet Nife, he motioned for Khaldorn to take the other.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Tell me of the curse, child,&quot; the god told him.  &quot;And I will tell you what I can.&quot;<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Khaldron began his tale, describing the runes and sharing the information that Innoruuk unknowingly gave to him.  He told of his sleeping companion, and what he knew of the circumstances which lead to his trip to the gods.  In the magnificent presence of the god, he found barriers of emotion broken down, and discovered himself telling things that he'd spoken to no one about, having nothing to do with his mission.  He told of his childhood, of the guilt he felt for all of his prior evil deeds, he spoke of the feelings of rejection from the people as he tried to make them see him for what he was.  All of these things poured from him to hang in the air.  After telling his tales, he felt strangely relieved, as if a wieght had been lifted from his shoulders.  For the first time since he'd begun talking he truely looked at the god before him.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Khaldron, this curse you've spoken of is very powerful.  You must find this stone which Innoruuk speaks of, and bring it to your friend.  Only with it's power might you turn back the curse.  You have done well in preventing it from spreading, and for that I commend you.  You must continue to watch, for it will spread if left untended.  This must not be allowed to happen.  Continue your vigil, and seek out the one who has caused this.  Only then will you be able to counteract such a curse, and see her healed.&quot;<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Khaldron thanked the diety, and stood.  He closed his etheric eyes, and found his body, his link to the physical realm.  Willing himself down into his form, he snapped his eyes open, looking around to get his bearings.  As he stood, Molina stirred in the bed.  He walked to the bedside, and took his friends hand, looking into her sleepy eyes.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Soon, we'll have you better.  Soon...&quot; <p><html>

