As I lay in my unrestful sleep, in the world between dreams and reality, I beg of Mother Tunare, to give me strength to go on, to help those that need me. In a shimmering form she lays her hand on my sore shoulder, and in a airy voice says &quot;the evil she has places within your flesh is beep, you will be able to continue, but you must find the cure quickly, keep your family close as the love you share with them will keep you strong&quot;. With those parting words I hear the voices of those around me, talking about what battles lie ahead.....<br>
<br>
&quot;Find the others&quot; I whisper, as I slowly come back to the world or life. &quot;Iszabelle is gathering more people to her side, she now has a cleric of your same abilities, working with her, someone I have met in the past and will support Iszabelle's cause.&quot; &quot;Arye is her name and she wishes us the same evil, her master does, be as weary of her as the others&quot;, I say as my body drifts back into the land of dreams..... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ada07e><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/urasheklightedge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rashek Lightedge</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lord Rashek, Guild Master</span><br>   <font color=#c54400>(8/4/00 2:54:48 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.goodnet.com/~saxon/minirash.jpg width=120 height=120></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: SHADOWS</span><hr size=1> Rashek stood at the edge of the Dark-Elven realm.  His eyes still stung from the noxious gases of the lavastorm.  The curse had begun.  The deep down fear that evil was taking a form had come to fruition.  That form had a name, &quot;Plague Bringers.&quot;<br>
<br>
That bitch Iszabelle was up to her old tricks.  That woman would continue to do what she did until someone stop her. Until someone snuffed out the filthy light of her existence once and for all.  Rashek's dearest wish was that he be the one to complete that joyous task.<br>
<br>
For now though, he needed his forces rallied behind him.  As they had dispersed across the land, bringing good, they had inadvertantly made themselves weak.  The smaller groups and individuals had become targets.  This could not be allowed to remain so.  Even now, Molina still lay weakened from the fetid touch of Iszabelle.  Rashek saw this to be his fault, his doing by want of his actions.<br>
<br>
He set forth now, his wife at his side, to bring his people together, and to hunt down and destroy Iszabelle and her diseased kin.  First port of call was to be his daughter and Khaldron, they would be the first needed.  Molina pure of heart, and Khaldron fighting valiantly with the Demons of his past.  Both equaly important to his plans.<br>
<br>
Light, as always, was dim in Nektulous.  Now was not the time to linger.  Righteous as he was, this was not a place to be, and hope to live for long.  Forces of darkness were strong here, a miriad of twisted souls inhabited the shadows around him.<br>
<br>
No, now was not the time to fight, the fight would be on his terms, not on those of the Plague Bringers.  Now was the time to decide what his terms would be.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
