<br>
&quot;KHALDRON YOU SHALL PAY FOR WHAT YOU HAVE DONE!&quot;<br>
<br>
Dekaarn clutched his staffs so tightly that splinters were pressing into his palms. Blood was running in rivulets down the deformed wood, mixing with the dried blood already there. His own, and others'. He stood there arms spread wide as in crucifixion, indeed the expression on his face would have matched the victim of such a fate. Of course, the victim wouldn't have had the gleam in his eyes that only pure hatred can bring. Dekaarn knew this because he had seen the expressions on the faces of his countless victims.<br>
<br>
Khaldron was an abomination. The bastard child of the Tier Dhal had forsaken his one true master, his one true family. FOR WHAT! for the friendship of the weak? the support of those ridiculous Fellowship fools?<br>
<br>
Of course the answer was yes. That was part of what seethed through Dekaarn's very blood. The rest was rage at what Khaldron had done. The treachorous little weasel had directly interfered with the actions of Iszabelle. <br>
<br>
Iszabelle, the one person Dekaarn respected. The one person Dekaarn saw any worth in. Iszabelle had been there when his family had been slain by those of the light. She had been there to guide his ways, to shape his mind. She had recognized pure unadulterated talent and intelligence and brutally shaped it to her needs. Rather than hate her for this, Dekaarn love her (as much as love had any meaning to him). She had given him purpose, direction. She had a vision he shared, a vision of hate.<br>
<br>
As Dekaarn shook with rage he heard his pet shifting behind him, it's bones almost creaking with the desire to rend flesh, any flesh.<br>
<br>
&quot;It's ok my sweet&quot; he said, the time has come. You shall have your flesh. <br>
<br>
&quot;Khaldron&quot; he whispered, shaking &quot;you will watch as I destroy those you love. You shall listen as they scream. And you shall stand by, helples, as I send their souls one by one to the netherworld.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;When you dream at night I will be there, When you walk in shadow I'll be there. When you think you are alone, you won't be. Fear me I tell you, because I am death incarnate!&quot; <br>
<br>
