</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ada07e><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uphyllisapaladin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phyllis a Paladin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://elfwood.lysator.liu.se/lothlorien/artists/mikael/anciol.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>BDF Member</span><br>   <font color=#c54400>(8/5/00 12:10:59 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://elfwood.lysator.liu.se/lothlorien/artists/mikael/anciol.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Death comes in many forms...</span><hr size=1> For centuries, the unbinder had been a dark magic of legend.  It came to Norrath through twisted magic’s that fey sorcerers had harnessed.  These very sorcerers did not seek this magic to help others, but to control all magic of this realm.  Deep, their magical incantations delved into the nether world seeking a source of power to animate the unbinder. Innoruuk , a selfish god with an acute hatred for the other prime powers, felt the fey sorcerers magical delving and opened up himself to it… As the sorcerers magical tendrils reached out, so did Innoruuk’s. Resulting in the death of all but one of the fey sorcerers, the chosen one. The war that ravaged the lands of Odus was all but forgotten, but by a few chosen.  Their existence has been unknown to all except the gods.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The water boiled up, spraying hot mud about scorching lesser beings to death, scaring all others with hideous burns.  Stones began to rise up from the muck, slowing assembling themselves into a towering monstrosity.  Phyllis, peering upward through trees and a magical field watched as her death slowly awoke.  <br>
<br>
“The Mother of ALL, please protect me and guide me to the truth.  Guide my blade to the heart of my enemies and smite them down with thy anger.  Guard my back and protect my soul, so that I might bring about your wishes…  The Mother of All, I pray to thee, “ Phyllis whispers to herself as she lowers her protective shield to begin combat…<br>
<br>
The sound of grating stones could be heard coming from the towering monstrosity.  A sound that resembled a voice, “You that has come to my resting place shall die if you fail my test!”  A giant foot of stone crashed down upon a tree next to Phyllis, knocking her off of her feet.  “Who are you, “ the giant stone golem asked?<br>
<br>
“I am Phyllis, first blood of the O’Connor family.  I claim the right of blood to that which you have,” shouting back to be heard over the grating sound of stone approaching her.<br>
<br>
“Tis a claim many have made and my swamp now flows with their blood, “ the giant stone golem stops its approach, “come and give your blood to me.  If you fail the test your blood shall join the others!”<br>
